# Copy to `.env` for local dev. On Netlify, set the same keys in Site settings → Environment variables.

# --- Report API (matches https://pu.playtonight.fun/api/payment/report/bucket-wise?date=YYYY-MM-DD) ---

# Option A — Direct calls from the browser (API must allow CORS for your dashboard origin):
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://pu.playtonight.fun
# VITE_API_REPORT_ENDPOINT=/api/payment/report/bucket-wise

# Option B — Same-origin + proxy (default on Netlify: /api/* → pu.playtonight.fun):
# Omit VITE_API_BASE_URL so the app uses your dashboard origin (e.g. https://nutradashboard.v1mobi.com).
# `npm run dev` proxies /api to pu.playtonight.fun via vite.config.ts.
# Endpoint defaults to /api/payment/report/bucket-wise in code if you omit this line.
# VITE_API_REPORT_ENDPOINT=/api/payment/report/bucket-wise

# Login: POST JSON to your auth API, or use fallback only for local demo (never commit real .env)
# VITE_AUTH_LOGIN_URL=https://your-api.example.com/api/auth/login
# VITE_FALLBACK_LOGIN_EMAIL=
# VITE_FALLBACK_LOGIN_PASSWORD=

# VITE_APP_TITLE=Nutra Dashboard
# VITE_DATE_RANGE_MAX_DAYS=31
# VITE_CONTACT_DETAILS_URL=
